flowRoot.flowPara: With stimulus-reaction-habits, for example if you get always a reward (m8, see also card b1, b2, b3, t1...) and after 1000 repetitions you will get punishment instead of a reward (m7) things like like here would happen. Or if a person invests a lot of time in one game and then would be banned forever from the Game, even worse if it was an unfair decision. The problem is if one has something like a spinal cord implant, then the whole reward /punishment thing becomes obsolete. So in both cases Computers can produce people that run amok. But with spinal-cord remote controlled he would not be the real murderer, and you can not blame only him, because the person that remote controlled him would just kill with the next "BOT". Try to find both, the BOT and the person that tries to make the "BOT" run amok. https://marclandolt.ch/ml_buzzernet/2016/04/25/vorstufe-zu-breivik/
